org.jasig.cas.ticket.proxy

Interface ProxyTicket

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, ServiceTicket, Ticket
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ProxyTicketDelegator, ProxyTicketImpl

    public interface ProxyTicket
extends ServiceTicket
    The ProxyTicket represents a CAS proxy ticket. A proxy ticket is an opaque string that a service uses as a credential to obtain access to a back-end service on behalf of a client. Proxy tickets are obtained from CAS upon a serviceâ€™s presentation of a valid ProxyGrantingTicket and a service identifier for the back-end service to which it is connecting.
